benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId} - Retrieve a bundle by id

covered: Valid Request scenarios (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04) with audit handling and default NONE
Query Parameters coverage (TC02, TC03, TC05, TC10) including FULL, MINIMAL, NONE, and unknown value
Error handling and edge cases (TC06 non-existent, TC07 invalid format, TC08 missing auth, TC09 invalid auth, TC11 empty DB, TC12 service unavailable, TC13 timeout, TC15 XSS in bundleId)
Boundary and compatibility cases (TC16 case-insensitive bundleId, TC17 backward compatibility without audit, TC18 concurrency, TC19 accessibility/readability, TC20 retry recovery)
Large data and performance considerations (TC14 large bundle data)
HTTP status and content validation (200s with JSON body, 400/404/401/503 responses as appropriate)
Audit information handling variations (FULL, MINIMAL, NONE)
gaps: Pagination handling for large datasets not covered (explicit pagination parameters, page size, page token scenarios)
Caching behavior and headers verification not covered (ETag, Cache-Control, Last-Modified)
Rate limiting / throttling scenarios not covered (burst requests, quota exceeded)
Authorization edge case beyond 401 (e.g., 403 Forbidden for insufficient permissions)
Validation of response schema beyond “valid Bundle object” (detailed schema tests, required fields, data types)
recommendations: Add dedicated pagination tests to verify correct page navigation, page size handling, and limits for large bundle datasets
Add tests that validate caching headers (ETag/Cache-Control) and cache validation/conditional requests
Add rate limiting and resilience tests (burst of requests, repeated retries, timeout backoffs)
Add authorization-specific tests for forbidden access (403) under valid authentication but insufficient permissions
Strengthen schema validation with explicit field-level assertions to ensure all required fields and data types are present in the Bundle object
